  "prompt": "How much does it cost to develop mobile application?",
  "response": "The cost of developing a mobile application can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\n1. App Complexity\n- Simple app: $5,000 - $20,000\n- Medium complexity app: $20,000 - $50,000\n- Complex app: $50,000 - $250,000+\n\n2. Factors Affecting Cost\n- Platform (iOS, Android, or cross-platform)\n- Features and functionality\n- Design complexity\n- Backend infrastructure\n- Integration with other systems\n- Maintenance and updates\n\n3. Development Approach\n- Freelancer: Generally cheaper ($10-$50/hour)\n- Local agency: Medium cost ($50-$150/hour)\n- Offshore development: Lower cost ($20-$80/hour)\n- Enterprise-level agency: Highest cost ($150-$250/hour)\n\n4. Additional Costs\n- App store registration\n- Design\n- Testing\n- Ongoing maintenance\n- Marketing\n\n5. Rough Estimate Ranges\n- Basic app: $5,000 - $20,000\n- Medium app: $20,000 - $50,000\n- Advanced/Enterprise app: $50,000 - $250,000+\n\nExact costs depend on specific project requirements and chosen development partner.",
